stages.title: Introduction & Discovery
stages.goal: However you're generating data objects - they all start out here. Your goal is to contact them and start them down the pipeline.

693a2cb694660564b3748ef6.title: Visit
693a2cb694660564b3748ef6.notes:
spoke with Jarred. Using Alapro mostly. Pretty loyal to him but he’s not able to do all makes and models. He also does his glass work.

I asked what we could do to see more work from him, he said nothing. He said he’ll try to throw us some bones and get us in the mix.

Lower priority account, lots of the cars are older

693a2cb694660564b3748ef4.title: Visit
693a2cb694660564b3748ef4.notes:
spoke with the new manager Steve. He is interested in getting more volume through the body shop. He also wants to put adas on his estimates so tagging and quote making will continue to be good here.

He asked about higher discount and I told him that with more volume we would be happy to increase the discount

693a2da594660564b3748efd.title: Visit
693a2da594660564b3748efd.notes:
Spoke with Drew and the writer. Nothing bad to say about John or his work.

They did say elitek does mechanical and they also like his work and don’t want to cut him out. They understand calibrating the major adas but SWS and parking sensor isn’t worth their time which is understandable. 

Net net elitek will continue to receive their vehicles that need mechanical and adas, we will receive just adas. Continue to tag cars until end of January and if volume doesn’t hold steady then we will stop tagging

6969314f2831205528417dc3.title: Visit
6969314f2831205528417dc3.notes: spoke to Randy the owner. They are basically doing everything in house. They do have some troubles with programming here and there and they’ll send it to the dealership. They’ve been extremely slow only 10 to 20 cars a month but they’re not even calibrating five of those.

696a84420f9b456ff83d2c69.title: Visit
696a84420f9b456ff83d2c69.notes:
spoke with Travis - Mccowns son who has been running the shop. There was a Nissan that we could not program that he sent to Nissan and they took care of it for $150. 

Additionally, we could not reprogram a Mercedes headlight and Aaron was able to. They have since been calling him. Those two mistakes plus being costly turned them away from us. 

I believe we can win this account back with damage control. Both Travis and Jeff are busy with customers

693a32c394660564b3748fad.title: Visit
693a32c394660564b3748fad.notes: Spoke with Alex, he had no idea you could calibrate from an R&I bumper. Explained all the money on the table he’s missing and he was dumbfounded. Need to follow up educate

693a32c494660564b3748fb0.title: Visit
693a32c494660564b3748fb0.notes: Nick was busy but may have two windshields upcoming for us

693a32c594660564b3748fb6.title: Visit
693a32c594660564b3748fb6.notes: Sharon is in the Elizabeth City location today

693a32c294660564b3748fa1.title: Visit
693a32c294660564b3748fa1.notes: Chad out with minor surgery but will be back 8am tomorrow

693a32c594660564b3748fb8.title: Visit
693a32c594660564b3748fb8.notes: Spoke with Michelle and technician. They have some inhouse capabilities but not everything. Sending to dealer whenever they can’t. They also have CCC and Mitchell. Send pricing structure and follow up!!

693a32c194660564b3748f9c.title: Visit
693a32c194660564b3748f9c.notes: Spoke with Reid the owner. Very solid dude, hasn’t looked at Trak once even though Brandon sends quotes. A lot of customer pays and odd jobs. Admitted he is still using Bernie but could be convinced to switch. Going to send excel sheet with everything they are missing

6978d933e35aa00484174d2d.title: Visit
6978d933e35aa00484174d2d.notes: spoke w Jerry the owner they are using auto metrics. Would 100% use us. Delivering 20-30 a month

6978d978e35aa00484174d31.title: Visit
6978d978e35aa00484174d31.notes: using Protech - 2 writers. Decent size shop doing 80 cars a month. Rebate would win. They do have a good relationship with protech but could be swayed not 100%. Statefarm DRP - liked software

697a68c30e7ab2298f67173b.title: Visit
697a68c30e7ab2298f67173b.notes:
​using dealerships for all calibrations making money on tow and markup. Guy is all about money. Elitek at 20%. Identifying off of codes and lights.

Will try us on a Honda and Buick that will both need calibrations for sure - 2025 models. He’s down for a process and wants to test out these two cars. Potential here for sure. Send Tyler or call next week

695e90d59b3927a3ec886e9b.title: Visit
695e90d59b3927a3ec886e9b.notes: Spoke very high level details with Alexia and met Steve/emailed him numbers. Doing roughly 30-40 cars a month and appears to be mostly newer cars. Boys with a towing company down the street but unsure if they are milking insurance deals. Sending everything to dealerships and hates how much the pricing costs and turn around time

697c3b764d728365acff095d.title: Visit
697c3b764d728365acff095d.notes: Spoke with George, told him about tech change and new deals we have going in Providence. He was very busy but said he has a car coming up for us but worried about space indoors. I mentioned during the summer that the outdoor lot would work perfect, then he got a phone call.

696716413566df5e105d48a4.title: Visit
696716413566df5e105d48a4.notes: spoke with Bill, sounded interested for problem cars. They have equipment in house but still run into problem cars a couple times a month. Keep trying to reach owner.

696716413566df5e105d48a4.title: Visit
696716413566df5e105d48a4.notes: jamal said they can do 95% of everything in house but will call next time they can’t

69671011ed53c970920a5473.title: Visit
69671011ed53c970920a5473.notes: Spoke with manager, Mike Edwards. He likes us a lot and is highly interested in pricing since we don’t charge for pre/post scans. Loyal to NuTech and they just struck a deal with state farm two weeks ago. Mike is open to it though and said anything can happen

693a2da694660564b3748f00.title: Visit
693a2da694660564b3748f00.notes:
Brandon is in market currently to help diagnose the Cadillac with John.

Eddie, Brad, and Greg spoke with Brandon over technician concerns - primarily turnaround time and confidence. They stated that Onsite could finish cars quickly and that they are delaying cars due to John’s work. Also, his confidence is not there.

Brandon reassured the shop that we will get to the bottom of John’s issues and see if there is a fix. They are still willing to work with us if there is improvement with John, before going back to Onsite. However, if this continues they will switch

6967149d3c5017a434e771ac.notes: Owned by Quality Collision Group. Decision goes above them if they can use a mobile company

6967149d3c5017a434e771ac.title: Visit
6967149d3c5017a434e771ac.notes: Met Dustin, spoke with him for a few minutes. Said he will give us a shot on any cars they can’t do with Airpro and seemed slightly interested in our scrubber

696729b83c5017a434e771ce.title: Visit
696729b83c5017a434e771ce.notes: Met owner rickey and his wife Pam. They are highly interested but emphasize quality and precision. They do anywhere from 10-20 scans a week, most needing calibrations. Using AutoPerfection but they aren’t loyal and are turning off from them. If we match their rebate of 30% they will give us a shot

693a346694660564b3748fe5.title: Visit
693a346694660564b3748fe5.notes: spoke with the manager it was a lady sitting at the front desk. There was an insurance adjuster sitting directly with her, so the conversation was extremely short. I mentioned that their current provider in the area we have information that he potentially is leaving this industry and so we wanted to follow up with her information if they do need a backup and if that is the case, she sounded very surprised by that and said she has not heard anything of that. They’ve been using him for the past 11 years and they’re very happy with it, but she would love to take her information if that does happen or to provide any overflow so I gave her my card and left. We didn’t get into any logistics at all since the adjuster was there.

693a24068975d9c25f4a2b41.notes: The owner of our shop called and personally has an issue with our technician, not related to our services. Will use us again if we switch tech

6998ad9387300e638ffdee33.title: Visit
6998ad9387300e638ffdee33.notes: Omar will definitely give us a shot and has his sisters car he needs to calibrate coming up soon. That being said, he does almost 100% customer pay work. Very low volume but wants to make us his primary if we are cheaper than towing to Andys (down the street)

69712d9c56081f7c334e72bc.title: Visit
69712d9c56081f7c334e72bc.notes: Would only use us for whatever Daniel can’t do (primarily fords). Leah was busy, come back next week

693a2cb794660564b3748ef9.title: Visit
693a2cb794660564b3748ef9.notes:
spoke with Jim and Theresa. They are loyal to us and are not incentivized to use all clear. They come out of Birmingham and flexed our turnaround time. All they could offer is 30% and they would charge for scans too.

Rudy is pushing 30% bc he’s ignorant. As long as the owner doesn’t hear about 30% we’re good. If he does, we’ll handle it. I promised them 25% if we can capture and identify everything

693a2cb594660564b3748ee6.notes:
went to the shop to consult anthony, the gm. he was not in and the owner, Barry Holcomb, was. I shared information with Barry and confirmed my information was accurate - sending two people to dealership for calibrations, lights on the dash only, inefficient, 0 profit etc... 

I asked him what he cared about and he said making money. I told showed him a profit analysis which he loved. He said to come by next tuesday to tag cars and show him what we can do. he asked our turn around time, where we are located, and how to schedule

693a2cb594660564b3748ee6.title: Visit
693a2cb594660564b3748ee6.notes:
spoke with Barry for feedback on the Nissan we did. He said everything was well and he liked our service. He was confused on what documentation to send to insurance and I told him the scrub report and invoice are best.

He mentioned he called CA RUSSELL to ask about us and our performance and there was nothing bad. He also asked about what process we have over there that works and I told him a combination of quoting and lot walks which he was open to. He wants to ease into things as this is new and slightly overwhelming. 

High probability of closing this account. Net net, follow up next week to speak with their team to implement a process and ease into it

693a2cb594660564b3748ee6.title: Visit
693a2cb594660564b3748ee6.notes:
spoke with Barry. He is very on board and just wants to ease into it. His biggest concern is getting reimbursed by insurance. He likes my consistency and fight.

Coming by on Monday to walk the lot.

693a2cb594660564b3748ee6.title: Visit
693a2cb594660564b3748ee6.notes:
spoke with Drake, Barry was not in. For him the biggest advantage was cycle time and getting the cars in and out. He requested a pricing sheet to which I sent to him which was helpful for him.

They like it so far and have admitted ignorance and that this is new for them and it takes easing into. They are not paid a monthly bonus on GP

693a2cb594660564b3748eec.title: Visit
693a2cb594660564b3748eec.notes: Come back. Heath was not available

693a2cb594660564b3748eed.title: Visit
693a2cb594660564b3748eed.notes:
spoke with Jace the GM over his email saying he wants to stick with Onsite Pass. He said our technician spent too much time and distracting his techs - this could be attributed to his unfamiliarity with our integration tactics which are normal with every shop.

He also mentioned he doesn’t want to completely cut out Onsite just because new guys are in town. He said process was good. Onsite gave him 30% and based on business maybe 35%. I told him we can match and we’ll revisit end of January

693a2cb594660564b3748eed.title: Visit
693a2cb594660564b3748eed.notes: Tagged 11 cars. Put them on post it notes and threw them on Jace desk. Short and sweet. We’ll see what we get

693a2cb594660564b3748eed.title: Visit
693a2cb594660564b3748eed.notes:
spoke with Jace - he said he wants to stick w onsite due to his relationship with their tech Jake I think his name was.

I asked what we could do to make him change his mind and he said discount. I asked if 40% to be primary would move him and he seemed to like it. I countered with free pre and post scans on all cars.

693a2cb794660564b3748ef7.title: Visit
693a2cb794660564b3748ef7.notes:
spoke with baker the owner. He said Deslerships are cheapest option and very quick.

Turnaround time seems to be his biggest thing.

Got a white Nissan he’ll try us out on. Tech to follow up on Monday to see if it’s out of paint

693a2cb794660564b3748ef7.title: Visit
693a2cb794660564b3748ef7.notes:
spoke with baker. Identified a grey Hyundai that will need blind spots and SVM in the front - SF on the back and progressive on the front,

Nissan that they are waiting on the brackets for that will need BSM. We should get both of those. JR good to stop by early next week to see what they got

696f8f338332117d85391b42.title: Visit
696f8f338332117d85391b42.notes: Spoke with Jason. Claims he can do most in house, calibrating 10-20 a week. Paying $350 per enterprise car. Offered 30% to match AllClear. Need to get a shot. Had allclear there 2 weeks ago. Biggest paint point is time it takes him to do the work

696f8f338332117d85391b42.title: Visit
696f8f338332117d85391b42.notes: Jason did not yell at me 🤠 spoke about Enterprise but he couldn’t give a verbal commitment

693a32c494660564b3748fb3.title: Visit
693a32c494660564b3748fb3.notes: Spoke with Russell but he was absolutely swamped. Wearing the front desk hat this week as well but hopefully someone starting soon.
